 <text id="A2540T">
  <front id="d2">
   <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
    <p>Hotchkiss writes a brief note to his wife, telling of bad weather. </p>
   </div1>
  </front>

  <body id="d4">
   <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
    <head>
     <name type="recipient">Sara A. Hotchkiss</name>
    </head>

    <opener>
     <dateline>
      <date value="1862-06-04">June 4<hi rend="super">th</hi> 1862</date>
      <name type="place">New Market</name>
     </dateline>
     <salute>Sara:</salute>
    </opener>

    <p>We have just come out of camp, all afloat from the tremendous rain of last night, Gen and all
     wet through, slept in the mud -- just got in the dry and just got your <orig reg="Blue"
     >Blu</orig> Letter, and just wrote to Nelson, and just opened this that I had sealed &amp;
     add this postscript -- and hope the sun has come out to you and the skies are brighter -- </p>

    <closer>
     <salute>cheer up</salute>
     <signed/>
    </closer>
   </div1>
  </body>
 </text>
